refinery                 package:fda                 R Documentation

_R_e_f_l_u_x _a_n_d _t_r_a_y _l_e_v_e_l _i_n _a _r_e_f_i_n_e_r_y

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     194 observations on reflux and "tray 47 level" in a distallation
     column in an oil refinery.

_F_o_r_m_a_t:

     A data.frame with the following components:  

     _T_i_m_e observation time 0:193 

     _R_e_f_l_u_x reflux flow centered on the mean of the first 60
          observations 

     _T_r_a_y_4_7 tray 47 level centered on the mean of the first 60
          observations 


_S_o_u_r_c_e:

     Ramsay, James O., and Silverman, Bernard W. (2006), _Functional
     Data Analysis, 2nd ed._, Springer, New York, p. 4, Figure 1.4, and
     chapter 17.

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e_s:

         attach(refinery)
     # allow space for an axis on the right 
         op <- par(mar=c(5, 4, 4, 5)+0.1)
     # plot uval 
         plot(Time, Reflux, type="l", bty="n")
     # add yval 
         y.u <- diff(range(Tray47))/diff(range(Reflux))
         u0 <- min(Reflux)
         y0 <- min(Tray47)

         lines(Time, u0+(Tray47-y0)/y.u, lty=3, lwd=1.5, col="red")
         y.tick <- pretty(range(Tray47))
         axis(4, at=u0+(y.tick)/y.u, labels=y.tick, col="red", lty=3,
                 lwd=1.5)
     # restore previous plot margins
         par(op)
         detach(refinery)

